intro: Maharanga hypoleuca, commonly known as the white maharanga, is a flowering plant native to New Zealand. It belongs to the Fabaceae family and is characterized by its distinctive white or pale yellow flowers. The plant typically grows in coastal and forested areas, preferring well-drained soils. Its leaves are trifoliate, consisting of three oval-shaped leaflets. Maharanga hypoleuca plays an important ecological role in its native habitat, supporting various insect and bird species.
